<article id="events">
  <h1>Natural History Related Events in Mole Valley</h1>

  <section id="butterfly" >

  <p>
    <%= image_tag "butterflies/Adonis-Blue-face.jpg", :class => 'butterfliesLeft',
                    :title => 'Adonis Blue face on. Copyright: Jeremy Early', :alt => "Adonis Blue butterfly face on" %>
  </p>
  <p>
    Mole Valley has a lively and active community of natural history enthusiasts. There are events
    that suite all levels of experience. We provide here some links that will keep you up to date
    with natural history related activities in Mole Valley.
  </p>
  <p>
    The RSPB Dorking and District Local Group organise regular events throughout the year that are
    open to all. You do not need to be an expert birdwatcher. Indeed you will find many are ideal
    for those that are wanting to get started. An up to date programme of events can be found
    <%= link_to("here", "http://www.rspb.org.uk/groups/dorkinganddistrict/events/", {:target => "_blank"}) %>.
  </p>
  </section>

  <section id="Adder" >
  <p>
  <%= image_tag "Adders-dancing.jpg", :class => 'butterfliesRight',
                    :title => 'Male Adders dancing. Copyright: Jeremy Early', :alt => "Male Adders dancing" %>
  </p>
  <p>
    Amphibians and Reptiles are important indicators of habitat quality. The Surrey Amphibian and Reptile
    Group is an extremely active and enthusiastic group that provides important support for some of our
    most threatened habitats. An up to date list of their events can be found
    <%= link_to("here", "http://surrey-arg.org.uk/SARG/30000-CommitteeTools/calendar/SARGcalendar.asp", {:target => "_blank"}) %>.
  </p>
  </section>

<% @events.each do |event| %>
  <section>
    <h1><%= event.title %></h1>
    <h2><%= event.date %></h2>
    <p><%= event.description %></p>
    
    <% if user_signed_in? %>
    <p>
      <%= link_to 'Show', event %>
      <%= link_to 'Edit', edit_event_path(event) %>
      <%= link_to 'Destroy', event, confirm: 'Are you sure?', method: :delete %></td>
  </p>
<% end %>
</section>
<% end %>

<section>
<% if user_signed_in? %>
<%= link_to 'New Event', new_event_path %>
<% end %>
<%= link_to 'List Comments', comments_path %>
</section>


</article>
